Reasoning: The paper deals with multiuser detection in CDMA systems, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of likelihood ascent search (LAS) algorithms and linear complexity also suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the proposed quasi LRS-CDMA approach may involve signal processing and optimization techniques, which could relate to the sub-category of signal and image processing (cs.SI).
